        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">Office of <persName>ALLEN &amp; CO.</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>82 BEAVER STREET</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>NEW YORK</placeName>, <date>Apl 24 1865</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear sir and friend.</p>
            <p>You gave me Bill for Books<lb/> $53 58/11111 to <add>?</add> I have added<lb/> $6=
                for 2 Bibles and enclose you<lb/> check for $59 58/11111 on Bk of New York,<lb/>
                Will you please get for me a full<lb/>
                <sic>sett</sic> of your Books, that is, 1 <sic>sett</sic><lb/> Prayer Books and 1
                    <sic>sett</sic> Parasah Books,<lb/> bound in Black and Gold, same as the<lb/>
                <sic>setts</sic> I had for <persName>Emma</persName> and
                    <persName>Charles</persName>.<lb/> I want them for myself, but no<lb/> name on
                them, and am in no<lb/> hurry for them. I read in Synagogue<lb/> on
                    <date>Sabbath</date> and had quite a good<lb/> attendance. I enclose you gold
                check for<lb/> 94 16/11111 which I received today of
                    <persName>Messrs<add>?</add><lb/> Dovale Abr</persName>. Please acknowledge
                receipt.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours vy truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
